## 📦 Local Development

1. **Clone the repository**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/bytesal/iSida.git
cd iSida

## Create virtual environment (Python 3.12)

python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

## Install dependencies

pip install -r requirements.txt

Create .env file with your DISCORD_TOKEN and MONGO_URI.

Run the bot

python main.py

## Auto‑Moderation Rules

The bot automatically enforces the following rules (users with Manage Messages permission are immune):

Rule	Threshold	Action
Spam	>5 messages in 5 seconds	Delete violating message + warn via DM
Discord Invites	Any discord.gg, discord.com/invite link	Delete message + warn
Mass Mention	>5 user/role mentions or @everyone	Delete message + warn
All violations are logged to the configured mod‑log channel.

📝 Logging
Set a mod‑log channel with /setmodlog. Every moderation action (kick, ban, warn, clear, slowmode, lockdown, unlock, auto‑mod violations) will be sent there as a detailed embed.

Example log embed includes:

Action type

Moderator (who performed the action)

Target member/user

Reason (if applicable)

Warning ID (for warns)

Timestamp

##⚠️ Important Notes
Python 3.12 is required – the bot uses audioop which was removed in Python 3.13. A runtime.txt file is included to force Python 3.12 on Railway.

The bot uses only slash commands; prefix commands are not supported.

To use the dashboard, you must also deploy the separate iSida Dashboard repository (FastAPI web interface). The dashboard is available at https://isida-dashboard.onrender.com.

